---
name: tkv2-button-variant
version: 1.0.0
backends: [int, js]
---

# tkv2 - button variant: colour selection for button primitives (std-ui-button-variant)

Slice `std-ui-button-variant` (`specs/std-ui-button-variant.md`): the four button
constructors (`signalButton`, `actionButton`, `signalLabelButton`,
`signalActionButton`) accept a new trailing `variant` param that `lower.ssc`
resolves to a themed background colour via `_buttonColor`. `View` is opaque to
`.ssc` (see `specs/std-ui-select.md` "Why no new extern def"), so — mirroring
`tests/conformance/std-ui-jobpanel.ssc`'s own TkNode-field-assertion style —
this conformance test asserts the `variant` field threads from each
constructor to its node unchanged, and that `lower()` does not throw for
every accepted variant plus an unrecognized string, on both lanes. The actual
rendered CSS background-colour swap (that the resolved colour genuinely
differs per variant) was verified empirically via `emit-js`; see
`specs/std-ui-button-variant.md` § Results.

(`std-ui-button-size` appended a 6th `size` field to each node after this
test was written; every pattern below binds it as `_` — unused here, this
file only asserts `variant` — see `tkv2-button-size.ssc` for the `size`
equivalent.)

[signal, setSignal](std/ui/primitives.ssc)
[signalButton, actionButton, signalLabelButton, signalActionButton](std/ui/input.ssc)
[SignalButtonNode, ActionButtonNode, SignalLabelButtonNode, SignalActionButtonNode](std/ui/nodes.ssc)
[lower](std/ui/lower.ssc)
[defaultTheme](std/ui/theme.ssc)

```scalascript
val sig      = signal("tkv2ButtonVariantSig", "")
val labelSig = signal("tkv2ButtonVariantLabel", "Go")
val handler  = setSignal(sig, "clicked")

// No `variant` argument at all — stays the pre-existing default ("primary"),
// backward compatible with every call site that predates this slice.
val defaultBtn = signalButton(sig, "x", "Default")
defaultBtn match
  case SignalButtonNode(_, _, label, _, variant, _) => println(label + ":" + variant)
  case _                                            => println("?")
val defaultView = lower(defaultBtn, defaultTheme)
println("default-built")

// Each accepted variant threads through actionButton's constructor to the
// node unchanged, and lowers without throwing.
val bPrimary = actionButton(handler, "Act", false, "primary")
bPrimary match
  case ActionButtonNode(_, label, _, variant, _) => println(label + ":" + variant)
  case _                                         => println("?")
val vPrimary = lower(bPrimary, defaultTheme)

val bSecondary = actionButton(handler, "Act", false, "secondary")
bSecondary match
  case ActionButtonNode(_, label, _, variant, _) => println(label + ":" + variant)
  case _                                         => println("?")
val vSecondary = lower(bSecondary, defaultTheme)

val bDanger = actionButton(handler, "Act", false, "danger")
bDanger match
  case ActionButtonNode(_, label, _, variant, _) => println(label + ":" + variant)
  case _                                         => println("?")
val vDanger = lower(bDanger, defaultTheme)

val bSuccess = actionButton(handler, "Act", false, "success")
bSuccess match
  case ActionButtonNode(_, label, _, variant, _) => println(label + ":" + variant)
  case _                                         => println("?")
val vSuccess = lower(bSuccess, defaultTheme)

val bWarning = actionButton(handler, "Act", false, "warning")
bWarning match
  case ActionButtonNode(_, label, _, variant, _) => println(label + ":" + variant)
  case _                                         => println("?")
val vWarning = lower(bWarning, defaultTheme)

// An unrecognized variant string threads through unchanged (the fallback to
// primary happens in lower.ssc's _buttonColor, not at construction) and must
// not crash either the node build or the lowering.
val bBogus = actionButton(handler, "Act", false, "bogus")
bBogus match
  case ActionButtonNode(_, label, _, variant, _) => println(label + ":" + variant)
  case _                                         => println("?")
val vBogus = lower(bBogus, defaultTheme)
println("action-variants-built")

// signalLabelButton / signalActionButton accept and thread `variant` the
// same way.
val lb = signalLabelButton(sig, "x", labelSig, false, "danger")
lb match
  case SignalLabelButtonNode(_, _, _, _, variant, _) => println("label-btn:" + variant)
  case _                                              => println("?")
val vLb = lower(lb, defaultTheme)

val sab = signalActionButton(handler, labelSig, false, "success")
sab match
  case SignalActionButtonNode(_, _, _, variant, _) => println("action-sig-btn:" + variant)
  case _                                           => println("?")
val vSab = lower(sab, defaultTheme)

println("button-variant-built")
```
